<paragraph blockId="19.[192,1439,1154,1242]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buquet" authorityYear="1859" box="[377,495,1155,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trestonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[377,495,1155,1178]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Trestonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently contains 21 described species. Nearns et al. (2011) provided color photographs for 
<specimenCount box="[393,481,1186,1211]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="generic" typeStatus="type">17 type</specimenCount>
specimens of this genus. We believe the genus is in need of a taxonomic revision (Nearns and Tavakilian in preparation).
</paragraph>
